        <b id="one">GMI’s Newest Member—the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia!</b>
        <p>
            The Steering Committee has officially approved the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia’s application
            to become a member of GMI, bringing total participation in GMI to 42 countries and
            the European Commission. As the world’s second-largest producer of petroleum, Saudi
            Arabia will appoint members to the Oil and Gas Subcommittee to share their extensive
            experience with flare management and gas recovery. The country will pursue opportunities
            in methane capture and reuse projects, including flare management, fugitive emissions
            control from pipelines and tanks, and gas recovery and utilization.
        </p>
